---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Reveal from '~/components/Reveal.astro';
import { buildHreflang } from '~/lib/i18n';

const hreflang = buildHreflang('/en/mission', 'en');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Our mission · Le Geai Informatique"
  description="Le Geai Informatique is the digital branch of the Le Geai house. A vision: minimalist, secure, turned towards experience and beauty. A model that funds art and welcomes interns into a humane setting."
  lang="en"
  hreflang={hreflang}
>
  <header class="page-head">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <Reveal>
        <h1>An idea, a mystique</h1>
      </Reveal>
      <Reveal delay={150}>
        <p class="motto">
          <em>Obscuritas nutrit flammam.</em>
          <span class="motto-fr">Darkness feeds the flame.</span>
        </p>
      </Reveal>
      <Reveal delay={300}>
        <p class="lead">
          Le Geai Informatique is not a web agency. It is the digital workshop
          of a wider house, founded on a simple exigence: to make well, to
          serve art and those who pass through.
        </p>
      </Reveal>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="block">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <Reveal>
        <h2>A branch, a workshop</h2>
        <p>
          Le Geai Informatique is the digital branch of Le Geai, a publishing
          house. What we build in code, in interfaces, in tools, does not serve
          only the client who commissions it; it sustains a design wider than
          the engagement, described further below.
        </p>
        <p>
          We have tools, skills and time. But above all we carry a vision and
          an empathy for those we accompany, along with a distaste for
          conventional websites, those large bland windows that all resemble
          one another. So we offer our own vision of computing.
        </p>
      </Reveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block block-soft">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <Reveal>
        <h2>Our vision</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Four exigences run through every one of our works.
        </p>
      </Reveal>
      <div class="pillars">
        <Reveal delay={100}>
          <div class="pillar">
            <p class="pillar-num">I</p>
            <h3>Minimalist</h3>
            <p>
              Each line of code, each pixel, each word must have its reason for
              being. The superfluous clutters, weighs down, blurs. We set it
              aside.
            </p>
          </div>
        </Reveal>
        <Reveal delay={150}>
          <div class="pillar">
            <p class="pillar-num">II</p>
            <h3>Secure</h3>
            <p>
              Your data and that of your clients is a responsibility, not a
              merchandise. We build soberly, without needless dependencies, in
              respect of the GDPR.
            </p>
          </div>
        </Reveal>
        <Reveal delay={200}>
          <div class="pillar">
            <p class="pillar-num">III</p>
            <h3>Turned towards use</h3>
            <p>
              A tool only has meaning if it serves someone. We design our works
              from your real activity, never from an abstract template.
            </p>
          </div>
        </Reveal>
        <Reveal delay={250}>
          <div class="pillar">
            <p class="pillar-num">IV</p>
            <h3>Beautiful</h3>
            <p>
              For beauty is not a luxury, it is a condition. We give each work
              the attention it deserves, in the line of what Dostoevsky wrote:
              beauty will save the world.
            </p>
          </div>
        </Reveal>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <Reveal>
        <h2>The pact</h2>
        <p>
          We work in computing to fund what we carry elsewhere: the publishing
          house, the printing of our books, the illustrators and artists we
          remunerate. That is also why our prices stay reasonable, where others
          inflate theirs.
        </p>
        <p>
          Becoming our client is not only having a website. It is obtaining a
          viable tool, designed for you, and at the same time funding art,
          jobs, and projects of the future at a humane scale.
        </p>
      </Reveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block block-soft">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <Reveal>
        <h2>Those who join the workshop</h2>
        <p>
          The founder knew the trial of the unfound internship, of time wasted
          knocking on the wrong doors. So we regularly welcome interns and,
          when the setting allows, apprentices. Our aim is to keep them on
          permanent contracts when the mission ends well.
        </p>
        <p>
          The setting we offer is designed to allow real work and a humane
          life at the same time:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-clean">
          <li>Mostly remote work, on-site possible when the need arises.</li>
          <li>No fixed imposed schedule, so long as the work is delivered on time and well done.</li>
          <li>The possibility of taking holidays, including for interns.</li>
          <li>Menstrual flexibility: leave taken without consequence on the mission or on rest days.</li>
          <li>An amicality that prevails over hierarchy, and a fluid working setting.</li>
        </ul>
      </Reveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <Reveal>
        <h2>The horizon</h2>
        <p>
          In time, we wish to open a shop kept by the Le Geai house. Our books
          would be sold there, along with old objects chosen for their
          aesthetic bearing, and we would open late in the evening to offer a
          refuge to those who need it. A place where the light stays on.
        </p>
      </Reveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mystique">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <Reveal>
        <p class="mystique-text">
          Le Geai Informatique is not a web shop. It is, to borrow Charles
          Péguy's word, a <em>mystique</em>: a living idea we try to uphold
          without letting it fall.
        </p>
      </Reveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <Reveal>
        <h2>The first conversation is offered</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Describe your activity, what you wish to build, what deserves to be
          reworked. We shall come back with a fair proposal.
        </p>
      </Reveal>
      <Reveal delay={150}>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a href="/en/contact" class="btn-primary">Discuss your project</a>
          <a href="/en/portfolio" class="btn-ghost">View the works</a>
        </div>
      </Reveal>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-head { padding: 8rem 1.5rem 4rem; text-align: center; }
  h1 { font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.8rem); }
  .motto {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .motto em {
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 1.8rem);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-dore);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .motto-fr {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    font-style: italic;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .lead {
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 2rem auto 0;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .block { padding: 5rem 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .block-soft { background: var(--color-surface-raised); }
  .block h2 {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3.4vw, 2.4rem);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .block p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.85;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }
  .block p em { color: var(--color-dore); font-style: italic; }
  .block .lead { margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 1.05rem; }

  .pillars {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.4rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .pillar {
    padding: 1.8rem 1.6rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }
  .pillar-num {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--color-dore);
    opacity: 0.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .pillar h3 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin-bottom: 0.7rem; }
  .pillar p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .list-clean { list-style: none; margin: 1rem 0; }
  .list-clean li {
    padding: 0.6rem 0 0.6rem 1.6rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    position: relative;
  }
  .list-clean li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 1.2rem;
    width: 10px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--color-dore);
  }

  .mystique {
    padding: 6rem 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    background: var(--color-surface-raised);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .mystique-text {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.2vw, 1.4rem);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 620px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }
  .mystique-text em { color: var(--color-dore); font-weight: 700; }

  .cta { padding: 6rem 1.5rem; text-align: center; }
  .cta h2 { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2rem); }
  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }
  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.85rem 2rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-noir);
    background: var(--color-dore);
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover { opacity: 0.85; }
  .btn-ghost {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.85rem 2rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    transition: all 0.4s ease;
  }
  .btn-ghost:hover { border-color: var(--color-dore); color: var(--color-dore); }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .pillars { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
